rror(), AgentCubeError))\"`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Implement `DataPlaneError` exception subclass\n35:   - Purpose: Exception for data plane communication errors\n36:   - File: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n37:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import DataPlaneError; print(isinstance(DataPlaneError(), AgentCubeError))\"`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: Utility Modules (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.1**: Implement `create_session()` helper in `utils/http.py`\n42:   - Purpose: Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n43:   - File: `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n44:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import create_session; s = create_session(); print(type(s))\"`\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `read_token_from_file()` helper in `utils/utils.py`\n47:   - Purpose: Read Kubernetes service account token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n48:   - File: `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n49:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_utils.py::test_read_token_from_file -v`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `get_logger()` helper in `utils/log.py`\n52:   - Purpose: Return configured logger instance for SDK operations\n53:   - File: `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n54:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.log import get_logger; log = get_logger('test'); print(type(log))\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.4**: Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` with exports\n57:   - Purpose: Export utility functions from utils package\n58:   - File: `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n59:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils import create_session, read_token_from_file, get_logger; print('OK')\"`\n60: \n61: ### Phase 3: ControlPlaneClient Implementation (ST-3)\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__` with base_url, timeout, connect_timeout\n64:   - Purpose: Initialize HTTP client for Workload Manager API\n65:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n66:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestControlPlaneClientInit -v`\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient` auth token resolution logic\n69:   - Purpose: Resolve auth_token from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n70:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n71:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestAuthTokenResolution -v`\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient` Authorization header when token present\n74:   - Purpose: Set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on session\n75:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n76:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestBearerAuthHeader -v`\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient._resolve_url()` helper\n79:   - Purpose: Resolve workload_manager_url from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n80:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n81:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestURLResolution -v`\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` method\n84:   - Purpose: POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body name, namespace, ttl, metadata\n85:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestCreateSession -v`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` return sessionId extraction\n89:   - Purpose: Return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise ValueError if absent\n90:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n91:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestCreateSession::test_create_session_missing_session_id -v`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.7**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` method\n94:   - Purpose: DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n95:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n96:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestDeleteSession -v`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.8**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` 404 handling\n99:   - Purpose: Return True on 404, log and return False on other failures\n100:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 750. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed]\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Exception Hierarchy (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentCubeError` base exception class\n  - Purpose: Define base exception for all AgentCube SDK errors","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775880274530,"end":1775880274550}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880274554,"sessionID":"ses_28549bd10ffe0MLhyFFrTz4Ju0","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab68245001rMElB0nNjecilu","messageID":"msg_d7ab66086001tBsflGQ9VkAuTU","sessionID":"ses_28549bd10ffe0MLhyFFrTz4Ju0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5c00a7ad8e57406c8fad7644f8a1eafe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane). The `CodeInterpreterClient` provides lifecycle management (session creation, cleanup), code execution, and file operations.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n18: \n19: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n24: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n25: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n30: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n31: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n36: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n42: \n43: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n48: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n49: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n50: \n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 230. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane). The `CodeInterpreterClient` provides lifecycle management (session creation, cleanup), code execution, and file operations.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880274533,"end":1775880274552}}}}
